<div class="content-header">Download and Install</div>

<div class="content">
    Download is available for Windows and Linux.
</div>

<div class="content">
The Windows executable comes with its own bundled Java JRE, and runs as a standalone application.
</div>

<div class="content">
    The Linux executable requires its own Java download.
</div>

<div class="content">
    The user is required to install and set up their own database.
    MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Oracle XE databases are supported.
    See the "Database Setup" section for details.
</div>

<div class="content">
    The installation also comes with a set of command-line scripts that execute the tasks found in the JavaFX interface.
    This allows users to handle conversion tasks like the bulk handling of files and database records,
    and to integrate tasks with other scripts.
    See the "Command-line Scripts" section for details.
</div>
